## Dependencies

- **Family L (Speech & Voice AI):** `/tts-design`, `/voice-clone`, `/prosody-control`,
  `/voice-eval`. The avatar's voice is upstream of every subsystem.
- **Family P sibling skills (downstream):** `/lip-sync`, `/gesture-synth`,
  `/expression-synth`, `/avatar-sign`.
- **Family G CV models:** face detection / parsing / FLAME fitting / MANO fitting
  for from-scratch face/body rigs.
- **Family O (Accessibility):** required if sign-language performance is enabled —
  `/sign-text`, `/sign-linguistics` feed `/avatar-sign`.
- **S9 — Eval-store schema:** EVAL-HUMANNESS.md writes baseline `task_id`s
  (`avatar-{slug}-{metric}`).
- **S12 — Study artifact format:** every output doc carries YAML frontmatter.
- **`/discover --domain avatar`:** refresh state-of-the-art before recommending.
- **`/autoplan-full`:** expands architecture into a build pipeline.
- Model checkpoints (downloaded by downstream skills, NOT here): FLAME, SMPL-X, MANO,
  MuseTalk, EMO, SadTalker, Wav2Lip, GENEA-SOTA, Audio2Gestures, EMOCA, DECA, MetaHuman.

---

## Important Rules

- **Never start training or rendering.** This skill ends at plan-on-disk.
- **Never download a model.** Checkpoints come from downstream skills.
- **Refuse physics-impossible specs.** 200ms streaming + diffusion + CPU isn't real;
  surface it before writing 4 docs the user can't ship.
- **Refuse license conflicts.** Commercial + research-only = refuse-and-clarify.
- **Refuse sign-performance without hand articulation.** Non-negotiable.
- **Cite specific versions.** "Gaussian Splatting" alone is not enough; pin a repo
  + commit / release.
- **Plan must reference S9 task_ids.** Eval harness will fail otherwise.
- **One use case per plan.** Don't write a "real-time AND cinematic" plan — those are
  two different architectures.
